## 4. File-by-File Breakdown

### 4.1 [app.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/app.py) — Flask Backend (Entry Point)

The HTTP layer. Creates the Flask server, defines routes, and delegates AI work to [RAGEngine](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#23-161) and persistence to `chat_store`.

**Key components:**
- **Singleton [RAGEngine](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#23-161)** — created once at startup, shared across all requests
- **`UPLOAD_DIR`** — PDFs saved to `uploads/` folder on disk
- **[init_db()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#30-70)** — called at startup to ensure SQLite tables exist

**Routes:**

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| GET | `/` | Serve the chat UI |
| GET | `/chats` | List all chats (newest first) |
| POST | `/chats/new` | Create a new empty chat |
| GET | `/chats/<id>` | Get all messages for a chat |
| DELETE | `/chats/<id>` | Delete a chat + messages |
| POST | `/upload` | Upload PDF, build vectors, link to chat |
| POST | `/ask` | Ask a question, save Q&A, auto-title |

**Design patterns:**
- **Singleton** — `engine = RAGEngine(...)` at module level avoids reloading the embedding model per request
- **Separation of Concerns** — routes in [app.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/app.py), ML in [rag_engine.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py), DB in [chat_store.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py)
- **Fail-Fast Validation** — multiple checks before processing (file exists? PDF? non-empty question?)

---

### 4.2 [rag_engine.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py) — The RAG Pipeline

This is the AI brain. Encapsulates the entire pipeline: extract → chunk → embed → store → retrieve → generate.

**Class: [RAGEngine](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#23-161)**

| Method | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| [__init__()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#25-40) | Loads MiniLM embeddings + ChatOllama LLM |
| [extract_text()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#43-52) | Pulls text from PDF pages using PyPDF2 |
| [chunk_text()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#55-63) | Splits text into 500-char chunks with 50-char overlap |
| [build_vectorstore()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#66-100) | Embeds chunks and stores in ChromaDB |
| [_build_chain()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#103-139) | Wires up retriever → prompt → LLM → parser (LCEL) |
| [load_pdf()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#142-155) | Orchestrates the full pipeline |
| [ask()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/rag_engine.py#156-161) | Runs the chain on a user question |

**RAG Chain Flow (LCEL):**

```
User Question
    │
    ├──→ Embed question (MiniLM-L6-v2, 384-dim vector)
    │     └── ChromaDB cosine similarity search → top 8 chunks
    │          └── format_docs() → join chunks into text
    │
    └──→ RunnablePassthrough() → question string
    │
    ▼
Prompt Template (strict rules: only use context, no hallucination)
    │
    ▼
Ollama llama3.2 (temperature=0, deterministic)
    │
    ▼
StrOutputParser → plain text answer
```

**Key parameters and why:**

| Parameter | Value | Reasoning |
|-----------|-------|-----------|
| Embedding model | `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` | Free, local, fast, 384-dim vectors |
| LLM | `llama3.2` via Ollama | Free, local, no API keys needed |
| Temperature | `0` | Deterministic — same question = same answer |
| Chunk size | `500` chars | Small enough for precise retrieval, big enough for context |
| Chunk overlap | `50` chars | Prevents cutting sentences at boundaries |
| Retriever k | `8` | 8 × 500 chars ≈ 4K context — well within LLM's window |

---

### 4.3 [chat_store.py](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py) — SQLite Persistence

Handles saving, loading, and deleting chats and messages. Uses SQLite because it's built into Python and needs zero setup.

**Database Schema:**

```
chats (one-to-many → messages)
  ├── id          TEXT PK    (UUID, 8 hex chars)
  ├── title       TEXT       (auto-named from first question)
  ├── pdf_name    TEXT       (uploaded PDF filename)
  └── created_at  TEXT       (ISO timestamp)

messages
  ├── id          INTEGER PK (auto-increment)
  ├── chat_id     TEXT FK    → chats.id (CASCADE delete)
  ├── role        TEXT       ("user" or "assistant")
  ├── content     TEXT       (message text)
  └── created_at  TEXT       (ISO timestamp)
```

**CRUD functions:**

| Function | SQL | Called by |
|----------|-----|----------|
| [init_db()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#30-70) | CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS | App startup |
| [create_chat()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#76-96) | INSERT INTO chats | POST `/chats/new` |
| [get_all_chats()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#98-112) | SELECT * ORDER BY DESC | GET `/chats` |
| [get_messages()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#114-129) | SELECT * WHERE chat_id ORDER BY ASC | GET `/chats/<id>` |
| [add_message()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#131-146) | INSERT INTO messages | POST `/ask` |
| [update_chat_title()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#148-162) | UPDATE chats SET title | POST `/ask` (first Q) |
| [update_chat_pdf()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_store.py#164-177) | UPDATE chats SET pdf_name | POST `/upload` |
| [delete_chat()](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/app.py#78-83) | DELETE FROM chats (cascades) | DELETE `/chats/<id>` |

