## 5. System Flow Diagrams

### PDF Upload Flow

```
User drops/picks a PDF
    │
    ├── Validate (is it a .pdf?)
    ├── Auto-create chat if none exists
    │
    ├── POST /upload (file + chat_id)
    │     ├── Save file to uploads/
    │     ├── extract_text() → raw text
    │     ├── chunk_text() → 500-char chunks with 50-char overlap
    │     ├── build_vectorstore() → embed + store in ChromaDB
    │     ├── _build_chain() → wire up LCEL pipeline
    │     └── update_chat_pdf() → link PDF name to chat
    │
    └── UI updates: show filename, chunk count, enable input
```

### Question-Answer Flow

```
User types question → clicks Send
    │
    ├── Display user message in chat
    ├── Show typing indicator
    │
    ├── POST /ask {question, chat_id}
    │     ├── chain.invoke(question):
    │     │     ├── Embed question → 384-dim vector
    │     │     ├── ChromaDB similarity search → top 8 chunks
    │     │     ├── Fill prompt template with context + question
    │     │     ├── Send to Ollama llama3.2
    │     │     └── Parse response → plain text
    │     ├── Save user message to DB
    │     ├── Save assistant message to DB
    │     └── Auto-title chat if first Q&A
    │
    ├── Remove typing indicator
    ├── Display AI answer
    └── Refresh sidebar (title may have changed)
```

---

## 6. Where State Lives

| State | Location | Lifetime |
|-------|----------|----------|
| Uploaded PDF files | `uploads/` on disk | Until manually deleted |
| Vector embeddings | `chroma_db/` on disk | Replaced on each new upload |
| RAG chain | `engine.chain` in memory | Replaced on each new upload |
| Chat metadata | [chat_history.db](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_history.db) → chats | Permanent until user deletes |
| Chat messages | [chat_history.db](file:///d:/MLDL/DL/chat_with_pdf/chat_history.db) → messages | Permanent until user deletes |
| Active chat ID | JS variable `currentChatId` | Per browser session |
| PDF ready flag | JS variable `pdfReady` | Per browser session |

